The Player (as a mind flayer) wraps their tentacles around Orpheus' face and brings their mouth over Orpheus' head. 
Player feeds CLUMSILY. Suckling noises.
Orpheus' eyes dart around in pain as his brain is consumed.
Once it's done, Orpheus' head flops to the side, his head empty.

Text.Value: You are a true hero.
There is no more for us to discuss.
I'm not becoming a mind flayer.
Since you drove the mind flayer away, you will need to become illithid in its place.
The resistance will not die with Orpheus. A new leader will rise.
Our people will remember you - the rebel illithid who stood beside their reborn prince and ended the Grand Design.
My people will remember you - the rebel illithid who stood beside their reborn prince and ended the Grand Design.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Orpheus descends to one knee in respect to whichever player is the mind flayer.

Text.Value: Then your choice is made - and so is mine.
All to wield these...

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Transformation over. Orpheus is Illithid and speaks telepathically now (like the Emperor.) The stones float over into his grasp. He looks at them with dismay for a beat before the next line.

Text.Value: Your very existence tests my self-restraint.
You still stand for Vlaakith? Can it be - a mind flayer in possession of its mental faculties?
*As the githyanki prince takes his blade, a silent cry pierces your head - a psionic scream to the Astral Plane.*
*As the githyanki prince takes his blade, a silent cry pierces your head. It's unlike any sensation you've ever felt.*

EditorData.AnimationTags: *REUSE*[ORPHEUS] Takes his sword from the ground, end in Draw/Stow Idle. <CodyM>
EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Orpheus calmly pulls a shortsword out of the rock nearby - his sword that was placed just out of reach that he's been staring at the whole time he's been imprisoned. He looks threatening.

Text.Value: We don't have time for revenge. We have bigger problems.
We don't have time for revenge. We have bigger problems.
Chk. The traitor's destiny is to adorn my queen's throne as a trophy.
Hta'zith!

EditorData.NodeContext: Heh-TAH-zith! Cry of attack.

Text.Value: I see you found it. And you had honour enough to use it. My people will thank you.
*Then - complete silence, as you are once again closed off from the Netherbrain's mind.*

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Player stands there as a mind flayer.

Text.Value: It's Lae'zel's word that's kept you from losing your mind, so show some gratitude.
It's Lae'zel's word that's kept you from losing your mind, so show some gratitude.
Well. And me. Look, I'm not long for this world anyway. I should transform. Do what needs to be done.

EditorData.NodeContext: A major moment. A major offer. A major sacrifice.

Text.Value: And you are a friend of ghaik.
Wait. Maybe you don't have to. It... it should be me.
I did not come to slay you; I'm here to restore you Orpheus, heir of All Skies.
I did not come to slay you; I'm here to restore you Orpheus, heir of All Skies.
But you? You I've misjudged. You were testing my honour. And in so doing, you have convinced me of yours.
Then you are truly ghaik, from skull to talon.
Yet here you stand, alive and still in control of your own mind. We have bigger problems now.
I am with you, Lae'zel. Today, Orpheus dies.
There is not.
I'm sorry, my prince. But I must assimilate you.
Gith'ka tavkim krash'ht.

EditorData.AnimationTags: *REUSE*[ORPHEUS] custom ending for Orpheus transforming into a Mindflayer.<CodyM>
EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Orpheus lifts his head to the stars, utters a prayer, and becomes full Illithid.
EditorData.NodeContext: 'Gith's light guides us' (Gith is his mother and the founder of all githyanki) [GITH-ka TAHV-keem KRASH-ht]

Text.Value: The traitor prince is dead, and we carry his power. Vlaakith gha'g shkath zai!

EditorData.NodeContext: VLAH-kith gawg shkaath ZAI!

Text.Value: If I'm to end the Netherbrain and its Grand Design, it seems I must call you ally. But I will never call you my prince.
You destroyed a githyanki crche.
The heretic child lives. Execute her as you said you would - then, we shall speak.
I'm sorry, zhak vo'n'fynh duj.

EditorData.NodeContext: zhak vone-fin-DOO, source of my joy. Laezel about to attack her lover.

Text.Value: You cannot, you will not!

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: Visceral and guttural response, stepping in front of Orpheus

Text.Value: Ch'k'l ghaik Vlaakith m' zath'ak!

EditorData.NodeContext: Mind flayer - abomination to Vlaakith!
EditorData.logicalname: OTHER PLAYER (5) IS ALREADY MIND FLAYER

Text.Value: And yet you will live. A ghaik thrall wearing the skin of his masters at long last.
Make no mistake - were it not for our common goal, I would strangle you where you stand.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Orpheus looks at you with distaste before speaking

Text.Value: You would ally with the seditious prince? Tsk'va!

EditorData.NodeContext: Incensed

Text.Value: Is this some sort of trick, or are you really so careless as to have misplaced it?
I stand with the Prince of the Comet. Attack, and you perish by my hand.
The empire will thrive under Vlaakith, as it has always done.
Under your watch, it almost succeeded.
*You feel sated. More than sated - complete. And ready to face the Netherbrain.*
She would have made an exquisite warrior, with proper indoctrination.
You will be the saviour of empires, not least my own.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: [Cody] Orpheus brings his right hand to his temple on "empires," looking down and pausing a beat, before dropping his hand and finishing the line.

Text.Value: The traitor prince. Vlaakith's would-be usurper.
Instead, witness the sight of true sacrifice.
So be it. But when the Grand Design is ended, I need the stones back.
Vlaakith will not let the Grand Design come to pass! In the Undying Queen, the githyanki are eternal.
It is etched in slate. So says Vlaakith, and so it must be.
Someone will need to turn into a mind flayer. Are you willing to do that?
*The hunger is too much to bear. Your nature is irresistible.*

EditorData.logicalname: Clicked on Orpheus a third time

Text.Value: An honourable offer - to sacrifice yourself to save the world.
Perhaps. And how many more millennia will we need to wait?
- but I cannot let you live!

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Orpheus |uses| the supreme tadpole and begins the Illithid transformation, which continues over the next nodes.

Text.Value: Let us return now to the city, and follow the path of the Netherbrain.
Yes.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Mindflayer player waves a hand, and opens a portal, ready for the party to leave.

Text.Value: After you, my friend.
Go ahead. I will follow.
Slay me then if you can, in the knowledge that if you win, the Netherbrain will take your mind.
I accept. Let's be allies.
I accept. Let's be allies.
You always were sensible. This heart inside me is about to blow. Doesn't matter which body it obliterates, right?
Allies? Shka'keth! I will hear no more of this nonsense.

EditorData.NodeContext: SHKA-keth

EditorData.logicalname: LAE"ZEL BECAME HOSTILE OUTSIDE OF DIALOG (KILLED VLAAKITH LAE"ZEL)

Text.Value: He must be consumed. Vlaakith's will above all.
You wouldn't dare - I'm too powerful. You need my help to kill the brain.
You're right. He is not only our prince, he is our best weapon against the brain.
You're right. He is not only your prince, he is our best weapon against the brain.
You understand nothing of duty, nor sacrifice.
Still searching? Hurry up.
Your honour guard attacked me. What was I supposed to do?
*Your mind and body whine with disappointment. But your soul lets out a gentle thrum of relief.*
You stole an unborn hatchling from your own people.
You stole an unborn hatchling from my people.
You've left me no choice, Lae'zel. I'm striking you down.
We need his power. This is the only way.
We face a Netherbrain. For there to be one way to defeat it is unlikely enough. There will not be another.
*You may have resisted once, but your hunger remains unsated. And this is a truly fine specimen. Best not to tempt fate.*

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Shot of Orpheus chained up, unresponsive. Same as N433.
EditorData.logicalname: Resisted consuming Orpheus once + clicked on Orpheus

Text.Value: I will allow the voice of the Absolute in. Once it reaches you, it will order you to transform.
When the brain is dead, I go my way - you go yours.

EditorData.NodeContext: Truly despondent but keeping strong and a bit quiet.

Text.Value: Please - whatever Prince Orpheus asks of us, we must obey.
Is this what you think? That I am an agent of the Illithid Empire?
You may address me as Your Majesty.
And it would take one wizard to unleash a cataclysm powerful enough to tear apart the brain's very being. We have no choice but to consider using the orb.

EditorData.NodeContext: Firm/determined - stepping up to the plate

Synopsis:
Orpheus is now freed from the player's assistance. They now have the option to take the Mind Flayer form, or to give Orpheus that responsibility. He is not really impressed with the tadpole in the player's head. 

It's possible the player would have fought Orpheus in Intermezzo before this point, so there should be some reactivity to it.
